{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":496,"text":"I'm very pleased to be here today"},{"time":2405,"text":"to talk to you all about how we might repair"},{"time":4959,"text":"the damaged brain,"},{"time":6995,"text":"and I'm particularly excited by this field,"},{"time":9237,"text":"because as a neurologist myself,"},{"time":11722,"text":"I believe that this offers one of the great ways"},{"time":13523,"text":"that we might be able to offer hope"},{"time":15455,"text":"for patients who today live with devastating"},{"time":18028,"text":"and yet untreatable diseases of the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21986,"text":"So here's the problem."},{"time":24076,"text":"You can see here the picture of somebody's brain"},{"time":26876,"text":"with Alzheimer's disease"},{"time":28408,"text":"next to a healthy brain,"},{"time":30327,"text":"and what's obvious is, in the Alzheimer's brain,"},{"time":32943,"text":"ringed red, there's obvious\ndamage -- atrophy, scarring."},{"time":37661,"text":"And I could show you equivalent pictures"},{"time":39378,"text":"from other disease: multiple sclerosis,"},{"time":41605,"text":"motor neuron disease, Parkinson's disease,"},{"time":44123,"text":"even Huntington's disease,"},{"time":46260,"text":"and they would all tell a similar story."},{"time":49229,"text":"And collectively these brain disorders represent"},{"time":51369,"text":"one of the major public health threats of our time."},{"time":54935,"text":"And the numbers here are really rather staggering."},{"time":59183,"text":"At any one time, there are 35 million people today"},{"time":62375,"text":"living with one of these brain diseases,"},{"time":65332,"text":"and the annual cost globally"},{"time":67871,"text":"is 700 billion dollars."},{"time":69891,"text":"I mean, just think about that."},{"time":71753,"text":"That's greater than one percent"},{"time":73240,"text":"of the global GDP."},{"time":75986,"text":"And it gets worse,"},{"time":77892,"text":"because all these numbers are rising"},{"time":80054,"text":"because these are by and large"},{"time":81512,"text":"age-related diseases, and we're living longer."},{"time":84700,"text":"So the question we really need to ask ourselves is,"},{"time":87095,"text":"why, given the devastating impact of these diseases"},{"time":91092,"text":"to the individual,"},{"time":92572,"text":"never mind the scale of the societal problem,"},{"time":95325,"text":"why are there no effective treatments?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":98906,"text":"Now in order to consider this,"},{"time":100884,"text":"I first need to give you a crash course"},{"time":103167,"text":"in how the brain works."},{"time":105492,"text":"So in other words, I need to tell you"},{"time":107378,"text":"everything I learned at medical school."},{"time":109434,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":111474,"text":"But believe me, this isn't going to take very long."},{"time":113712,"text":"Okay? (Laughter)"},{"time":116167,"text":"So the brain is terribly simple:"},{"time":118136,"text":"it's made up of four cells,"},{"time":121183,"text":"and two of them are shown here."},{"time":122985,"text":"There's the nerve cell,"},{"time":124498,"text":"and then there's the myelinating cell,"},{"time":126038,"text":"or the insulating cell."},{"time":127536,"text":"It's called oligodendrocyte."},{"time":130026,"text":"And when these four cells work together"},{"time":131815,"text":"in health and harmony,"},{"time":133674,"text":"they create an extraordinary\nsymphony of electrical activity,"},{"time":137642,"text":"and it is this electrical activity"},{"time":139882,"text":"that underpins our ability to think, to emote,"},{"time":143255,"text":"to remember, to learn, move, feel and so on."},{"time":146599,"text":"But equally, each of these individual four cells"},{"time":149940,"text":"alone or together, can go rogue or die,"},{"time":155030,"text":"and when that happens, you get damage."},{"time":157275,"text":"You get damaged wiring."},{"time":158490,"text":"You get disrupted connections."},{"time":161554,"text":"And that's evident here with the slower conduction."},{"time":165712,"text":"But ultimately, this damage will manifest"},{"time":168175,"text":"as disease, clearly."},{"time":170657,"text":"And if the starting dying nerve cell"},{"time":173755,"text":"is a motor nerve, for example,"},{"time":175571,"text":"you'll get motor neuron disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177986,"text":"So I'd like to give you a real-life illustration"},{"time":180609,"text":"of what happens with motor neuron disease."},{"time":184017,"text":"So this is a patient of mine called John."},{"time":186546,"text":"John I saw just last week in the clinic."},{"time":189559,"text":"And I've asked John to tell us something \nabout what were his problems"},{"time":193183,"text":"that led to the initial diagnosis"},{"time":195082,"text":"of motor neuron disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196721,"text":"John: I was diagnosed in October in 2011,"},{"time":201670,"text":"and the main problem was a breathing problem,"},{"time":205250,"text":"difficulty breathing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206943,"text":"Siddharthan Chandran: I don't know if you\ncaught all of that, but what John was telling us"},{"time":209203,"text":"was that difficulty with breathing"},{"time":211443,"text":"led eventually to the diagnosis"},{"time":213537,"text":"of motor neuron disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216390,"text":"So John's now 18 months\nfurther down in that journey,"},{"time":219954,"text":"and I've now asked him to tell us something about"},{"time":222187,"text":"his current predicament."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224476,"text":"John: What I've got now is \nthe breathing's gotten worse."},{"time":227336,"text":"I've got weakness in my hands, \nmy arms and my legs."},{"time":233033,"text":"So basically I'm in a wheelchair most of the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237853,"text":"SC: John's just told us he's in a wheelchair"},{"time":240679,"text":"most of the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242803,"text":"So what these two clips show"},{"time":245021,"text":"is not just the devastating\nconsequence of the disease,"},{"time":247777,"text":"but they also tell us something about"},{"time":249320,"text":"the shocking pace of the disease,"},{"time":251620,"text":"because in just 18 months,"},{"time":254932,"text":"a fit adult man has been rendered"},{"time":257628,"text":"wheelchair- and respirator-dependent."},{"time":260959,"text":"And let's face it, John could be anybody's father,"},{"time":263264,"text":"brother or friend."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265451,"text":"So that's what happens when the motor nerve dies."},{"time":267704,"text":"But what happens when that myelin cell dies?"},{"time":272304,"text":"You get multiple sclerosis."},{"time":274524,"text":"So the scan on your left"},{"time":276343,"text":"is an illustration of the brain,"},{"time":279066,"text":"and it's a map of the connections of the brain,"},{"time":281917,"text":"and superimposed upon which"},{"time":283884,"text":"are areas of damage."},{"time":285258,"text":"We call them lesions of demyelination."},{"time":287449,"text":"But they're damage, and they're white."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290281,"text":"So I know what you're thinking here."},{"time":291796,"text":"You're thinking, \"My God, this bloke came up"},{"time":294304,"text":"and said he's going to talk about hope,"},{"time":296235,"text":"and all he's done is give a really rather bleak"},{"time":298744,"text":"and depressing tale.\""},{"time":300308,"text":"I've told you these diseases are terrible."},{"time":301903,"text":"They're devastating, numbers are rising,"},{"time":304564,"text":"the costs are ridiculous, and worst of all,"},{"time":306691,"text":"we have no treatment. Where's the hope?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":308977,"text":"Well, you know what? I think there is hope."},{"time":311522,"text":"And there's hope in this next section,"},{"time":313916,"text":"of this brain section of somebody else with M.S.,"},{"time":316211,"text":"because what it illustrates"},{"time":317739,"text":"is, amazingly, the brain can repair itself."},{"time":320212,"text":"It just doesn't do it well enough."},{"time":322790,"text":"And so again, there are two\nthings I want to show you."},{"time":324915,"text":"First of all is the damage of this patient with M.S."},{"time":328341,"text":"And again, it's another one of these white masses."},{"time":331824,"text":"But crucially, the area that's ringed red"},{"time":335262,"text":"highlights an area that is pale blue."},{"time":337485,"text":"But that area that is pale blue was once white."},{"time":340311,"text":"So it was damaged. It's now repaired."},{"time":343922,"text":"Just to be clear: It's not because of doctors."},{"time":346684,"text":"It's in spite of doctors, not because of doctors."},{"time":349001,"text":"This is spontaneous repair."},{"time":351184,"text":"It's amazing and it's occurred"},{"time":352732,"text":"because there are stem cells in the brain, even,"},{"time":355946,"text":"which can enable new myelin, new insulation,"},{"time":359120,"text":"to be laid down over the damaged nerves."},{"time":361449,"text":"And this observation is important for two reasons."},{"time":365936,"text":"The first is it challenges one of the orthodoxies"},{"time":369176,"text":"that we learnt at medical school,"},{"time":370805,"text":"or at least I did, admittedly last century,"},{"time":374425,"text":"which is that the brain doesn't repair itself,"},{"time":376996,"text":"unlike, say, the bone or the liver."},{"time":380117,"text":"But actually it does, but it\njust doesn't do it well enough."},{"time":383616,"text":"And the second thing it does,"},{"time":385258,"text":"and it gives us a very clear direction \nof travel for new therapies --"},{"time":389233,"text":"I mean, you don't need to be a rocket scientist"},{"time":390952,"text":"to know what to do here."},{"time":392472,"text":"You simply need to find ways of promoting"},{"time":395405,"text":"the endogenous, spontaneous\nrepair that occurs anyway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399929,"text":"So the question is, why, if we've known that"},{"time":402386,"text":"for some time, as we have,"},{"time":404343,"text":"why do we not have those treatments?"},{"time":408637,"text":"And that in part reflects the complexity"},{"time":410756,"text":"of drug development."},{"time":413367,"text":"Now, drug development you might think of"},{"time":415401,"text":"as a rather expensive but risky bet,"},{"time":418125,"text":"and the odds of this bet are roughly this:"},{"time":420078,"text":"they're 10,000 to one against,"},{"time":422675,"text":"because you need to screen\nabout 10,000 compounds"},{"time":425480,"text":"to find that one potential winner."},{"time":427551,"text":"And then you need to spend 15 years"},{"time":429468,"text":"and spend over a billion dollars,"},{"time":430966,"text":"and even then, you may not have a winner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434109,"text":"So the question for us is,"},{"time":435788,"text":"can you change the rules of the game"},{"time":437379,"text":"and can you shorten the odds?"},{"time":439928,"text":"And in order to do that, you have to think,"},{"time":441972,"text":"where is the bottleneck in this drug discovery?"},{"time":444802,"text":"And one of the bottlenecks is \nearly in drug discovery."},{"time":447915,"text":"All that screening occurs in animal models."},{"time":451877,"text":"But we know that the proper \nstudy of mankind is man,"},{"time":455336,"text":"to borrow from Alexander Pope."},{"time":457440,"text":"So the question is, can we study these diseases"},{"time":459811,"text":"using human material?"},{"time":462199,"text":"And of course, absolutely we can."},{"time":464262,"text":"We can use stem cells,"},{"time":465791,"text":"and specifically we can use human stem cells."},{"time":468591,"text":"And human stem cells are these extraordinary"},{"time":470695,"text":"but simple cells that can do two things:"},{"time":473097,"text":"they can self-renew or make more of themselves,"},{"time":475891,"text":"but they can also become specialized"},{"time":477949,"text":"to make bone, liver or, crucially, nerve cells,"},{"time":480548,"text":"maybe even the motor nerve cell"},{"time":482388,"text":"or the myelin cell."},{"time":484548,"text":"And the challenge has long been,"},{"time":486069,"text":"can we harness the power,"},{"time":488041,"text":"the undoubted power of these stem cells"},{"time":490326,"text":"in order to realize their promise"},{"time":492344,"text":"for regenerative neurology?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":493971,"text":"And I think we can now, and the reason we can"},{"time":496900,"text":"is because there have been\nseveral major discoveries"},{"time":499808,"text":"in the last 10, 20 years."},{"time":501545,"text":"One of them was here in Edinburgh,"},{"time":503157,"text":"and it must be the only celebrity sheep, Dolly."},{"time":507269,"text":"So Dolly was made in Edinburgh,"},{"time":508894,"text":"and Dolly was an example"},{"time":510577,"text":"of the first cloning of a mammal"},{"time":513791,"text":"from an adult cell."},{"time":515739,"text":"But I think the even more significant breakthrough"},{"time":518544,"text":"for the purposes of our discussion today"},{"time":521466,"text":"was made in 2006 by a Japanese scientist"},{"time":523955,"text":"called Yamanaka."},{"time":525552,"text":"And what Yamaka did,"},{"time":526856,"text":"in a fantastic form of scientific cookery,"},{"time":529288,"text":"was he showed that four ingredients,"},{"time":531326,"text":"just four ingredients,"},{"time":533189,"text":"could effectively convert any cell, adult cell,"},{"time":536376,"text":"into a master stem cell."},{"time":538618,"text":"And the significance of this is difficult to exaggerate,"},{"time":541602,"text":"because what it means that\nfrom anybody in this room,"},{"time":543842,"text":"but particularly patients,"},{"time":545646,"text":"you could now generate"},{"time":546977,"text":"a bespoke, personalized tissue repair kit."},{"time":549703,"text":"Take a skin cell, make it a master pluripotent cell,"},{"time":552651,"text":"so you could then make those cells"},{"time":554390,"text":"that are relevant to their disease,"},{"time":556829,"text":"both to study but potentially to treat."},{"time":559471,"text":"Now, the idea of that at medical school --"},{"time":561533,"text":"this is a recurring theme, isn't \nit, me and medical school? —"},{"time":564158,"text":"would have been ridiculous,"},{"time":565976,"text":"but it's an absolute reality today."},{"time":568035,"text":"And I see this as the cornerstone"},{"time":570169,"text":"of regeneration, repair and hope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573346,"text":"And whilst we're on the theme of hope,"},{"time":575296,"text":"for those of you who might have failed at school,"},{"time":577437,"text":"there's hope for you as well,"},{"time":579662,"text":"because this is the school report of John Gerdon."},{"time":582158,"text":"[\"I believe he has ideas about becoming a scientist;\non his present showing this is quite ridiculous.\"]"},{"time":583370,"text":"So they didn't think much of him then."},{"time":584806,"text":"But what you may not know is that he \ngot the Nobel Prize for medicine"},{"time":587664,"text":"just three months ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590216,"text":"So to return to the original problem,"},{"time":592782,"text":"what is the opportunity of these stem cells,"},{"time":594925,"text":"or this disruptive technology,"},{"time":596586,"text":"for repairing the damaged brain,"},{"time":598140,"text":"which we call regenerative neurology?"},{"time":600271,"text":"I think there are two ways you can think about this:"},{"time":602698,"text":"as a fantastic 21st-century drug discovery tool,"},{"time":606146,"text":"and/or as a form of therapy."},{"time":608963,"text":"So I want to tell you a little bit about both of those"},{"time":610990,"text":"in the next few moments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613439,"text":"Drug discovery in a dish is how people often"},{"time":615470,"text":"talk about this."},{"time":616700,"text":"It's very simple: You take a patient with a disease,"},{"time":619627,"text":"let's say motor neuron disease,"},{"time":621446,"text":"you take a skin sample,"},{"time":623203,"text":"you do the pluripotent reprogramming,"},{"time":626261,"text":"as I've already told you,"},{"time":628352,"text":"and you generate live motor nerve cells."},{"time":630869,"text":"That's straightforward, because that's what"},{"time":632603,"text":"pluripotent cells can do."},{"time":634340,"text":"But crucially, you can then compare their behavior"},{"time":637296,"text":"to their equivalent but healthy counterparts,"},{"time":639719,"text":"ideally from an unaffected relative."},{"time":641749,"text":"That way, you're matching for genetic variation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644991,"text":"And that's exactly what we did here."},{"time":647338,"text":"This was a collaboration with colleagues:"},{"time":649261,"text":"in London, Chris Shaw; in the U.S., \nSteve Finkbeiner and Tom Maniatis."},{"time":652784,"text":"And what you're looking at, and this is amazing,"},{"time":655306,"text":"these are living, growing, motor nerve cells"},{"time":658106,"text":"from a patient with motor neuron disease."},{"time":660349,"text":"It happens to be an inherited form."},{"time":662274,"text":"I mean, just imagine that."},{"time":663973,"text":"This would have been unimaginable 10 years ago."},{"time":666454,"text":"So apart from seeing them\ngrow and put out processes,"},{"time":669808,"text":"we can also engineer them so that they fluoresce,"},{"time":672250,"text":"but crucially, we can then\ntrack their individual health"},{"time":675309,"text":"and compare the diseased motor nerve cells"},{"time":677829,"text":"to the healthy ones."},{"time":679701,"text":"And when you do all that and put it together,"},{"time":683188,"text":"you realize that the diseased ones,"},{"time":685287,"text":"which is represented in the red line,"},{"time":687075,"text":"are two and a half times more likely to die"},{"time":690696,"text":"than the healthy counterpart."},{"time":693401,"text":"And the crucial point about this is that you then have"},{"time":696044,"text":"a fantastic assay to discover drugs,"},{"time":699633,"text":"because what would you ask of the drugs,"},{"time":701542,"text":"and you could do this through a high-throughput"},{"time":703303,"text":"automated screening system,"},{"time":705712,"text":"you'd ask the drugs, give me one thing:"},{"time":708158,"text":"find me a drug that will bring the red line"},{"time":710983,"text":"closer to the blue line,"},{"time":712873,"text":"because that drug will be a high-value candidate"},{"time":716092,"text":"that you could probably take direct to human trial"},{"time":718992,"text":"and almost bypass that bottleneck"},{"time":721579,"text":"that I've told you about in drug discovery"},{"time":723980,"text":"with the animal models,"},{"time":725793,"text":"if that makes sense. It's fantastic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728446,"text":"But I want to come back"},{"time":730010,"text":"to how you might use stem cells directly"},{"time":732059,"text":"to repair damage."},{"time":733834,"text":"And again there are two ways to think about this,"},{"time":735659,"text":"and they're not mutually exclusive."},{"time":737674,"text":"The first, and I think in the long run"},{"time":739964,"text":"the one that will give us the biggest dividend,"},{"time":742193,"text":"but it's not thought of that way just yet,"},{"time":744797,"text":"is to think about those stem cells that are already"},{"time":748053,"text":"in your brain, and I've told you that."},{"time":749893,"text":"All of us have stem cells in the brain,"},{"time":751747,"text":"even the diseased brain,"},{"time":753382,"text":"and surely the smart way forward"},{"time":755000,"text":"is to find ways that you can promote and activate"},{"time":757497,"text":"those stem cells in your brain already"},{"time":759533,"text":"to react and respond appropriately to damage"},{"time":762720,"text":"to repair it."},{"time":764004,"text":"That will be the future."},{"time":765436,"text":"There will be drugs that will do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":768309,"text":"But the other way is to effectively parachute in cells,"},{"time":772572,"text":"transplant them in,"},{"time":774376,"text":"to replace dying or lost cells, even in the brain."},{"time":778854,"text":"And I want to tell you now an experiment,"},{"time":780942,"text":"it's a clinical trial that we did,"},{"time":782836,"text":"which recently completed,"},{"time":784692,"text":"which is with colleagues in UCL,"},{"time":787209,"text":"David Miller in particular."},{"time":789964,"text":"So this study was very simple."},{"time":791877,"text":"We took patients with multiple sclerosis"},{"time":794979,"text":"and asked a simple question:"},{"time":796517,"text":"Would stem cells from the bone marrow"},{"time":798191,"text":"be protective of their nerves?"},{"time":799914,"text":"So what we did was we took this bone marrow,"},{"time":803759,"text":"grew up the stem cells in the lab,"},{"time":805976,"text":"and then injected them back into the vein."},{"time":808315,"text":"I'm making this sound really simple."},{"time":810115,"text":"It took five years off a lot of people, okay?"},{"time":813222,"text":"And it put gray hair on me"},{"time":814910,"text":"and caused all kinds of issues."},{"time":816391,"text":"But conceptually, it's essentially simple."},{"time":820414,"text":"So we've given them into the vein, right?"},{"time":823721,"text":"So in order to measure whether\nthis was successful or not,"},{"time":827354,"text":"we measured the optic nerve"},{"time":829102,"text":"as our outcome measure."},{"time":830788,"text":"And that's a good thing to measure in M.S.,"},{"time":832553,"text":"because patients with M.S. sadly suffer"},{"time":834626,"text":"with problems with vision --"},{"time":836098,"text":"loss of vision, unclear vision."},{"time":838288,"text":"And so we measured the size of the optic nerve"},{"time":840371,"text":"using the scans with David Miller"},{"time":842425,"text":"three times -- 12 months, six months,"},{"time":844523,"text":"and before the infusion --"},{"time":846139,"text":"and you can see the gently declining red line."},{"time":849265,"text":"And that's telling you that\nthe optic nerve is shrinking,"},{"time":851493,"text":"which makes sense, because their nerves are dying."},{"time":853836,"text":"We then gave the stem cell infusion"},{"time":856142,"text":"and repeated the measurement twice --"},{"time":858243,"text":"three months and six months --"},{"time":859882,"text":"and to our surprise, almost,"},{"time":861855,"text":"the line's gone up."},{"time":864011,"text":"That suggests that the intervention"},{"time":866542,"text":"has been protective."},{"time":868439,"text":"I don't think myself that what's happened"},{"time":870356,"text":"is that those stem cells have made new myelin"},{"time":872392,"text":"or new nerves."},{"time":873856,"text":"What I think they've done is they've promoted"},{"time":876001,"text":"the endogenous stem cells, or precursor cells,"},{"time":878610,"text":"to do their job, wake up, lay down new myelin."},{"time":882061,"text":"So this is a proof of concept."},{"time":884360,"text":"I'm very excited about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":886985,"text":"So I just want to end with the theme I began on,"},{"time":889474,"text":"which was regeneration and hope."},{"time":891464,"text":"So here I've asked John"},{"time":893234,"text":"what his hopes are for the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":895532,"text":"John: I would hope that"},{"time":897286,"text":"sometime in the future"},{"time":899086,"text":"through the research that you people are doing,"},{"time":901526,"text":"we can come up with a cure"},{"time":903735,"text":"so that people like me can lead a normal life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":907559,"text":"SC: I mean, that speaks volumes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910154,"text":"But I'd like to close by first of all thanking John --"},{"time":912693,"text":"thanking John for allowing me to share"},{"time":914422,"text":"his insights and these clips with you all."},{"time":917592,"text":"But I'd also like to add to John and to others"},{"time":920127,"text":"that my own view is, I'm hopeful for the future."},{"time":922704,"text":"I do believe that the disruptive technologies"},{"time":925056,"text":"like stem cells that I've tried to explain to you"},{"time":927114,"text":"do offer very real hope."},{"time":928935,"text":"And I do think that the day that we might be able"},{"time":930698,"text":"to repair the damaged brain"},{"time":932134,"text":"is sooner than we think."},{"time":933423,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":935226,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}